    <meta name="description" content="The Tigris-Euphrates river system is a great river system of southwestern Asia. It comprises the Tigris and Euphrates rivers, which follow roughly parallel courses through the heart of the Middle East. The lower portion of the region that they define, known as Mesopotamia, was one of the cradles of civilization." />
